headline: Does KeyCorp’s Earnings Beat, Buybacks, and New Debt Issuance Change The Bull Case For KeyCorp (KEY)?
summary: In January 2026, KeyCorp reported fourth-quarter and full-year 2025 results showing higher net interest income and a return to profitability, alongside $104 million in net loan charge-offs and completion of a $200 million share repurchase program. The bank also issued $750 million of fixed-to-floating senior unsecured notes due 2037, while reshaping its board with director retirements and a new lead independent director, underscoring an emphasis on funding flexibility, governance refresh,...
